# Workspace confinement

All work must stay under the project (workspace) root. Do not create, read, or edit files outside the workspace. Framework rules (e.g. NORMS, AI-AGENT-CONTRACT) also apply; for this project, path and directory constraints in this rule take precedence.

## File paths

- Only use paths under the workspace. No paths to home directory, `/tmp`, or other locations outside the project.
- When suggesting or running file operations, use the workspace as the root.

## Terminal commands

- Run terminal commands with the workspace as the current working directory (project root).
- If a command needs a specific working directory, use a path under the workspace (e.g. `output/`, `data/`).

## Downloads and generated files

- **downloads/** — Files fetched from the internet (wget, curl, browser downloads).
- **data/** — Input data, datasets, catalogs.
- **output/** — Plots, tables, exported results, logs.

Use these subdirectories instead of home or `/tmp`. Create them on first use if they do not exist.
